  "prompt": "What is months at level in Accenture?",
  "response": "In Accenture, \"months at level\" typically refers to the amount of time an employee has spent in a specific role or position within the company. This metric can be important for performance evaluations, promotions, and career progression. Different levels within the company might have expected time frames for which employees should stay in their roles before moving up, as well as criteria for demonstrating readiness for advancement.\n\nIf you need more specific information about how \"months at level\" is applied at Accenture or its significance in terms of promotions or evaluations, it would be best to refer to internal resources or human resource guidelines provided by Accenture itself.",
